<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title><![CDATA[herrbischoff/awesome-macos-command-line Daily Updates RSS Feed]]></title><description><![CDATA[Track your favorite github awesome repo, not just star it.]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com</link><generator>GatsbyJS</generator><lastBuildDate>Tue, 29 Jun 2021 23:45:53 GMT</lastBuildDate><item><title><![CDATA[herrbischoff/awesome-macos-command-line Nov 9th, 2020]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>Package Managers</h2>
<li><a href="http://www.finkproject.org">Fink</a> - The full world of Unix Open Source
software for Darwin. A little outdated.</li>
<li><a href="https://brew.sh">Homebrew</a> - The missing package manager for OS X. The most
popular choice.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.macports.org">MacPorts</a> - Compile, install and upgrade either
command-line, X11 or Aqua based open-source software.</li>
<h2>System</h2><h4>Create Bootable Installer</h4>
<li>For confirmation before erasing the drive, remove <code>–-nointeraction</code> from the
command.</li>
<li>The optional <code>–-downloadassets</code> flag is new in macOS 10.14 (Mojave). It
downloads assets which may be required during installation, like updates.</li>
<li>The <code>–-applicationpath</code> flag is deprecated since macOS 10.14 (Mojave) and
will throw an error if used.</li>
<h2>Terminal</h2><h3>Alternative Terminals</h3>
<li><a href="https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty">Alacritty</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">32k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":32000,"repo":"jwilm/alacritty"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Cross-platform,
GPU-accelerated terminal emulator.</li>
<li><a href="https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/">kitty</a> - Modern, GPU-accelerated terminal
emulator.</li>
<h2>Terminal</h2><h4>Bash</h4>
<li><a href="https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/">Homepage</a> - The default shell for OS X
and most other Unix-based operating systems.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/Bash-it/bash-it">Bash-it</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/Bash-it/bash-it" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">12.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":12271,"repo":"Bash-it/bash-it"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Community Bash framework,
